#viewer-visibility.doc-content 
    
    h1 Toggle Component Visibility
    .definition Hide and unhide components in the viewer. The components may not be shown at all or in transparency mode if ghosting mode is enabled.
    
    h2 viewerHideModel(partNumber, params) 
    p Hides all instances of the component with defined part number. This will call the function viewerHideModels with exact same parameters as described next.
    p.code 
        span.indent-1 viewerSetColor('002771', {
        span.indent-2 usePath : false
        span.indent-1 });
    
    h2 viewerHideModels(partNumbers, params) 
    p Hides all instances of all components within list of part numbers.
    p.code 
        span.indent-1 viewerHideModels(['002771','003881','009119'], {
        span.indent-2 usePath : false
        span.indent-1 }) ;
    p Use the params object (JSON) to enable the required behavior using the parameters listed below.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Parameter 
                th Description 
                th Type
                th Default Value
            tr 
                td ghosting
                td When components get hidden in the viewer, they can be ghosted instead by setting this parameter to true (this behavior is overwritten by the ghosting toggle in the viewer toolbar if enabled)
                td Boolean 
                td true  
            tr 
                td usePath
                td Enable this option if paths are provided instead of part numbers, enabling to interact with definded instances of a part number. You can use method getBOMItemPath in BOM display to get the matching path of a selected item.
                td Boolean 
                td false

    h2 viewerUnhideModel(partNumber, params) 
    p Unides all instances of the component with defined part number. This will invoke function viewerHideModels (described next) with exact same parameters.
    p.code viewerUnhideModel('002771') ;
    
    h2 viewerUnhideModels(partNumbers, params) 
    p Hides all instances of all components within list of part numbers.
    p.code 
        span.indent-1 viewerUnhideModelss(['002771','003881','009119'] {
        span.indent-2 'fitToView' : true
        span.indent-1 }) ;
    p Use the params object (JSON) to enable the required behavior using the parameters listed below.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Parameter 
                th Description 
                th Type
                th Default Value
            tr 
                td fitToView
                td This will refresh the viewer after components got unhidden to fit these components into screen
                td Boolean 
                td true
            tr 
                td highlight
                td Highlight the components being unhidden by defined color
                td Boolean 
                td true                     
            tr 
                td resetColors
                td If set to true, all colors of all components will be reset before
                td Boolean 
                td true    
            tr 
                td usePath
                td Enable this option if paths are provided instead of part numbers, enabling to interact with definded instances of a part number. You can use method getBOMItemPath in BOM display to get the matching path of a selected item.
                td Boolean 
                td false                    
            tr 
                td color
                td Defines the color to be used for highlighting the given components
                td Array (red, green, blue, transparency)
                td [240, 0, 0, 0.5]   
    h2 viewerUnhideAll(params) 
    p This will show all components
    p.code viewerUnhideAll();
    p Use the params object (JSON) to enable the required behavior using the parameters listed below.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Parameter 
                th Description 
                th Type
                th Default Value
            tr 
                td fitToView
                td This will refresh the viewer after components got unhidden to fit all components into screen
                td Boolean 
                td true
            tr 
                td resetColors
                td If set to true, all colors of all components will be reset before
                td Boolean 
                td true           
            tr 
                td keepHidden
                td If the hide feature is enabled in the viewer toolbar, the components will remain hidden and reset button will remain
                td Boolean 
                td true